Earthquake AI

     This project is an application designed to allow users to try cosmetics from various brands in one place. Users can select cosmetics that suit their skin tone and try out colors through the app to ensure the chosen shades are as accurate and close to reality as possible. The application is designed for ease of use, allowing users to search for cosmetics based on their preferences or use the recommendation mode tailored to their skin tone, with the ability to test colors directly within the app.

For this project :

Developed website with JavaScript ,HTML ,CSS ,SQL

The face-api.js library is utilized for facial detection and analysis.

Deploy to Netlify

Demo : NIAU demo

NIAU

     EarthQuake AI is an AI system for the short-term prediction of the severity (intensity) and damage (destruction) of earthquakes. It analyzes key parameters such as reaction, magnitude, and depth to make accurate predictions. This project uses the K-nearest neighbor classifier (KNN) to train the model, splitting the data 70% for training and 30% for testing and achieving 99% accuracy. Additional metrics such as precision, recall, and F1 score are also used to comprehensively evaluate the performance of the model. The API is developed with Flask on Jupyter Notebook and managed with Nginx to connect it to a domain. The TMUX library ensures that the Jupyter Notebook server runs continuously.

The API is hosted on Google Cloud Platform, while the frontend is developed with the React framework and connected to the API using Axios.

For this project :

Developed website with Python , JavaScript , HTML , CSS

Website : https://earthquack-ai-sigma.vercel.app/
